==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uropoetic
<hw>U`ro*po*et"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[1st
<ets>uro-</ets> + Gr. <?/ to make.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Producing, or favoring the
production of, urine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or
designating, a system of organs which eliminate nitrogenous waste matter
from the blood of certain invertebrates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uropygial</ent>⟦br⟧
